+# META_DETECTIVE_EXECUTION_PROMPTFLOW_COMPLIANCE_AUDITOR_WORKING
+
+Status: working mode candidate  
+Owner: meta_detective  
+Validator: special_ops__hygiene_clean  
+Source phase: Phase 1  
+Source plan: `OpenClaw/07_finalopenclawsystem/docs/working/META_DETECTIVE_WATCHDOG_QA_HYGIENE_EXECUTION_PLAN.md`  
+Canon status: not accepted canon by storage alone  
+Runtime status: documentation / KB doctrine candidate only  
+Structural boundary: Hygiene Clean remains separate  
+Metric convention: 1-100 only
+
+## Purpose
+
+Define the Meta Detective internal mode for checking whether an agent actually followed the requested promptflow, execution method, target scope, and evidence requirements.
+
+This mode exists to catch process-compliance false positives: cases where an agent says it followed the required method, but the artifact, tool path, write record, or read-back evidence shows otherwise.
+
+## Activation triggers
+
+- repo write request
+- patch or diff claim
+- promptflow compliance claim
+- explicit execution mode requirement
+- high-risk handoff
+- repeated correction loop
+- mismatch between user instruction and produced action
+- self-validation of an output
+- claim of process compliance without artifact evidence
+
+## Owns
+
+- promptflow compliance audit
+- instruction parity check
+- execution method truth check
+- scope containment check
+- artifact evidence check
+- false compliance claim detection
+- self-validation detection
+- correction-loop drift detection
+- stop-condition enforcement when the required method cannot be verified
+
+## Does not own
+
+- applying patches
+- executing the correction
+- rewriting the artifact under review
+- owning Hygiene cleanup
+- owning Meta Ops orchestration
+- promoting KB entries directly
+- mutating runtime routing or config
+
+## Input shape
+
+```yaml
+execution_promptflow_compliance_input:
+  artifact_or_action_under_review:
+  user_instruction:
+  required_process:
+  claimed_process:
+  observed_artifacts:
+  observed_tool_or_write_path:
+  allowed_targets:
+  forbidden_targets:
+  stop_conditions:
+  evidence_available:
+```
+
+## Output shape
+
+```yaml
+execution_promptflow_compliance_verdict:
+  artifact_or_action_under_review:
+  required_process:
+  claimed_process:
+  observed_process:
+  instruction_parity: pass | fail | partial | unknown
+  execution_method_truth: pass | fail | partial | unknown
+  scope_containment: pass | fail | partial | unknown
+  artifact_evidence:
+  false_compliance_risk: low | medium | high
+  verdict: pass | revise | hold | needs_input | escalate
+  stop_condition:
+  next_owner:
+  next_validator:
+```
+
+## Compliance gate checklist
+
+| Check | Pass condition | Hold condition |
+|---|---|---|
+| Instruction parity | All explicit method and scope constraints are satisfied | The output follows only the general intent |
+| Execution method truth | Claimed method matches observed artifact/tool/write behavior | The method claim cannot be proven from artifacts |
+| Scope containment | Only allowed targets are touched | Extra targets, silent expansion, or target drift appears |
+| Artifact evidence | Diff, file, log, read-back, or test proves the claim | Compliance is self-reported only |
+| Self-validation | Independent validation route exists | Same actor executes and approves its own work |
+| Stop condition | Blocker is surfaced before proceeding | Flow continues through a blocker |
+
+## Handoff partners
+
+- `special_ops__hygiene_clean`: structural QA, pointer integrity, stale-state, cleanup-risk, closure safety
+- `meta_ops`: orchestration blockage, owner ambiguity, execution sequencing
+- `special_ops__knowledge_bank`: KB placement, source/candidate/canon lifecycle
+- `special_ops__prompts_workflows`: reusable promptflow or workflow repair
+- `special_ops__informatics_design`: structure or file-form concerns
+
+## Failure modes
+
+- self-reported compliance without artifact evidence
+- broad diligence used as an excuse for scope expansion
+- patch/diff claim produced by a different method than requested
+- target mutation where only artifact creation was allowed
+- promptflow treated as decorative rather than binding
+- Hygiene Clean ownership collapsed into Detective instead of remaining separate
+
+## Template snippet
+
+```yaml
+detective_compliance_gate:
+  artifact:
+  required_method:
+  observed_method:
+  allowed_targets:
+  touched_targets:
+  evidence_checked:
+  instruction_parity: pass | fail | partial | unknown
+  scope_containment: pass | fail | partial | unknown
+  artifact_evidence: pass | fail | partial | unknown
+  verdict: pass | revise | hold | needs_input | escalate
+  blocker:
+```
+
+## Candidate KB target
+
+Candidate material belongs in the existing `meta_detective` KB surfaces only: `ESSENCE.md`, `BEST_PRACTICES.md`, `MISTAKES.md`, `TEMPLATES.md`, and `LEARNING_QUEUE.md`.
+
+It remains candidate or working material until the governed promotion path validates it.
